report.measDesc: The dataset is converted to file geodatabase (FGDB) format using tools in ArcGIS. The geometry is checked, and if needed repaired.
After processing, the data set is checked for drawing display and number of records and file sizes compared with source materials.

Horizontal positional accuracy is dependent on geographic area. In most areas, accuracy is between 5 and 25 meters (16 and 82 feet). In some areas, accuracy is off by up to several tens of meters (100 feet or more). In the poorest areas, accuracy is off by up to 100 meters (328 feet).

srcCitatn.resAltTitle: TomTom MultiNet North America Administrative Areas v. 2011.12 and v. 2010.03

prcStep.stepDesc: The following steps were performed by Esri: Extracted the dataset from StreetMap Premium for ArcGIS North America TomTom. Removed all Canada and Mexico records. Added the field STATE and coded it by overlaying on Data and Maps 2015 U.S. States. Added the field ZIP_TYPE and calculated its values to "ZIP Code Area" for records that found a match in Data and Maps 2016 U.S. ZIP Code Areas (Five-Digit) and "Post Office or large volume customer" for records that didn't find a match. Added the field SQMI and calculated its values for records that found a match in U.S. ZIP Code Areas (Five-Digit). Added the field POPULATION (alias POP2015) and added and calculated the field POP_SQMI (alias POP15_SQMI). Put "-99" values into all number type fields for records where there were no data.

stepSrc.srcDesc: Sources: 1) SMP for ArcGIS NA TT; 2) Esri Data; 3) TomTom MultiNet North America Administrative Areas v. 2011.12 and v. 2010.03.
